`.github/workflows/` holds this repo's CI/CD automation; currently it contains a single pipeline that publishes a static visualization site to GitHub Pages.

The one workflow, `deploy-viz.yml`, couples three things that must stay in sync outside this directory: a Rust binary target named `viz-data` (writes `out/viz-data.json`), the file layout it assembles under `_site/` (`viz/index.html` + `out/viz-data.json`), and `viz/index.html`'s relative fetch path back to that JSON. Changing any one of the binary name, its output path, or the fetch path silently breaks the deployed site — none of these are checked at CI time, only at page-load time in production. The toolchain is pinned externally via `rust-toolchain`/`rust-toolchain.toml`, not in the workflow itself, so a Rust version bump happens there, not here. Deploys are serialized via the `pages` concurrency group.

No intent.md exists for this directory to check against.